The paper deals with scheduling tasks in a computing environment, which is a problem commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of dynamic speed scaling and sleep state capabilities suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The problem of minimizing energy consumption is related to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of approximation algorithms and computational complexity analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.PF (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
